\section*{First-person pronoun: I}

In Sanskrit, the first-person words are a little similar to those in
English. For example, some of the Sanskrit words start with ``aa,''
whose sound is similar to the sound of the English word ``I.'' And
some of the Sanskrit words start with ``m,'' like the English words
``me,'' ``my,'' and ``mine.''

If you know languages such as Spanish, French, or Italian, you may
